  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Input field contains several lines of text. If tap on chat then keyboard is hidden. If tap on the text then keyboard is not shown (this is issue). Only if tap on the end of the last line then keyboard is shown. Text:\r\nShort line [my comment: hit Enter to go to next line]\r\nNext line started after hit enter and goes to the new line without any enter  [my comment: hit Enter to go to next line]\r\nThis is again started with enter and goes to new line without enter\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nIf tap on any place in the input field then keyboard is shown\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nIf tap on the text of several lines then keyboard is not shown. Only if tap on the end of the last line then keyboard is shown\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7MHNWbXNXOGhFejA\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open 1-1 chat\r\n- Type text as in description. Do not type comments in []\r\n- Tap on chat screen. Keyboard will be hidden\r\n- Tap on first or second lines of the text. Expected: Keyboard is shown\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.6d76\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS",
